3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"KuCoin calculates APT funding rates using a time-weighted average of the premium between perpetual and spot prices over each 8-hour period. The funding fee is exchanged directly between long and short position holders, with KuCoin taking no commission from the funding payments. Positions held through funding time automatically participate in the funding exchange, with fees calculated on the notional position value."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","APT","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"APT represents significant arbitrage potential due to Aptos network developments driving volatility and sentiment shifts. The token's Layer 1 status creates correlation patterns with broader smart contract platform narratives, often resulting in funding rate premiums during ecosystem announcements or partnership news."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"APT funding rates on KuCoin have shown consistent positive bias during Aptos ecosystem growth phases, particularly around validator updates and DeFi protocol launches. The 8-hour interval structure creates opportunities for arbitrageurs to capitalize on sustained funding premiums that often persist for 2-3 funding cycles. Monthly analysis reveals funding rates ranging from -0.5% to +2.1% during peak volatility periods, with average rates hovering around +0.01% to +0.05% during neutral market conditions."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"KuCoin's APT perpetuals frequently trade at premiums to spot during bullish Aptos news cycles, creating profitable short perpetual/long spot arbitrage setups. The exchange's decent altcoin liquidity supports position sizes up to $50k without significant slippage impact. Cross-exchange arbitrage becomes viable when KuCoin's funding rates diverge from Binance or OKX by more than 0.1% on an 8-hour basis, accounting for trading fees and transfer costs."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"APT's mid-tier trading volume on KuCoin creates liquidity constraints during high volatility periods, potentially impacting position entry and exit timing. The exchange's regulatory uncertainties following 2023 SEC charges add counterparty risk considerations for larger arbitrage positions. Auto-deleveraging risk increases during extreme funding rate periods above 1%, as highly leveraged positions may face forced liquidation. Position sizing should account for KuCoin's insurance fund limitations compared to tier-1 exchanges."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What is the funding interval for APT perpetuals on KuCoin?","answer":"KuCoin applies funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC. You'll pay or receive funding only if you hold a position through these specific times."},{"question":"How do KuCoin's APT funding rates compare to other exchanges?","answer":"KuCoin typically shows slightly higher funding rate volatility due to its smaller APT perpetual market compared to Binance. This creates more frequent arbitrage opportunities but requires careful position sizing due to liquidity constraints."},{"question":"What fees apply to APT perpetual trading on KuCoin?","answer":"KuCoin charges 0.02% maker fees and 0.06% taker fees for APT perpetuals. Funding payments between traders incur no additional exchange commission, making the true arbitrage cost dependent only on trading fees."},{"question":"Is there auto-deleveraging risk for APT positions on KuCoin?","answer":"Yes, during extreme market conditions KuCoin may auto-deleverage profitable positions to cover losses from bankrupt accounts. This risk is higher for APT due to its mid-tier liquidity profile compared to major cryptocurrencies."}]}]
